WARNING. Sensitive content. Progressively more gruesome as you swipe ▶️ This majestic girl had a sneaky habit, unbeknownst to her owners. It wasn't until we detected a large mass in her abdomen that we had reason to investigate. Imaging revealed a gastric foreign body of unknown origin.

On gastrotomy, she was found to have 56 pieces of hair band, string, elastic and laces all clumped into one mass!

Fortunately she has recovered well from her surgery and is being watched 24/7 to make sure she's not up to her old habits! 🧶🐈

WimbleDONE 🥎

Ok it's hardly a candid shot but very important reason behind it.

Bulldogs, like Teddy, are one of a
number of brachycephalic (flat faced) breeds. These dogs are prone to Brachycephalic Obstructive Airway Syndrome (BOAS) which
can cause major breathing issues

Teddy today underwent a functional assessment including an examination and exercise tolerance test. This can allow grading of the severity and therefore appropriate treatment,
which often means corrective surgery.
Despite being cared for by an extremely responsible owner Teddy would still benefit from surgery.

There's a lot of media attention on these issues at present and the veterinary profession has a duty to take a more proactive position to promote optimum welfare in these susceptible breeds.
.
